% Social Golfer instance 6-3-8: 18 golfers in 6 groups of 3, scheduled for 8
% weeks so no pair of golfers ever shares a group more than once. Each golfer
% shares a group with group_size - 1 = 2 others per week, so 9 weeks would need
% 18 distinct partners out of only 17 others — 8 weeks is the most any 6-3
% schedule can reach. model.mzn pins weeks 1-2 with a transversal symmetry break.

n_groups   = 5;
group_size = 3;
n_weeks    = 7;
